config.title: ABOUT THE DATA

variables.Description: Number of unemployed people as a percentage of the labor force (population that is either working or actively looking for work).
variables.Insights: Employment among workforce participants is directly related to economic opportunity. It also indicates if the economy is operating at its full productive potential.
variables.Source: Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS), Economy at a Glance Tables

variables.Description: Number of jobs added or lost compared to selected baseline.
variables.Insights: Knowing the fluctuations in the number of jobs by industry can inform what occupations are in high demand, and could inform workforce development strategies.
variables.Source: Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS), Economy at a Glance Tables

variables.Description: Total amount of dollars spent by consumers in locations registered in SafeGraph's POI credit and debit card transactions data.
variables.Insights: Consumer spending is a key indicative of the current economy and can help identify struggling commercial corridors. This data point can guide strategic investment decisions to improve commercial activity in the city.
variables.Geography: City of Baltimore, Community Statistical Areas
variables.Source: Dewey Data, SafeGraph POI transaction data

variables.Description: Total number of credit and debit card transactions in locations registered in SafeGraph's POI data.
variables.Insights: Although consumer spending provides information about the amount of dollars spent, the number of transactions can serve as proxy of demand. A analysis of these two data points provides a more comprehensive look into consumer behavior and commercial activity.
variables.Geography: City of Baltimore, Community Statistical Areas
variables.Source: Dewey Data, SafeGraph POI transaction data

variables.Description: Total number of new businesses formed. Collected by Data Axle from secretaries of state, county courthouses, utility providers, departments of revenue, departments of taxation, local business and legal journals, and other sources that record new business transactions.
variables.Insights: New businesses bring jobs and revenue to the local economies by offering local products, paying sales and property tax, and using local vendors and supporting services. This data point is indicative of the conditions the local economy has to foster new businesses, providing insights for the implementation of entrepreneurship support programs.
variables.Source: Data Axle USA New Businesses Dashboard

variables.Description: Perception of businesses that reported rent to be a burden as a monthly expenditure. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: The perception of rent burden among small businesses helps to identify the pressures that puts them at risk of failing. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance to small businesses, create affordable rental commercial properties, provide down payment assistance programs, and more.

variables.Description: Percentage of businesses that reported paying rent in full last month. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: Small businesses failing to pay rent in full and on time are at risk of failing. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance to small businesses, create affordable rental commercial properties, provide down payment assistance programs, and more.

variables.Description: Percentage of businesses that reported paying more on rent now than six months ago. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: Increases in small businesses' rent costs are helpful to identify the pressures that puts them at risk of failing. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance to small businesses, create affordable rental commercial properties, provide down payment assistance programs, and more.

variables.Description: Estimated time businesses reported would be capable to continue operations with cash currently at hand if revenue stopped tomorrow. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: Understanding cash flow capacity is helpful to identify the level of risk small businesses are at in case of crisis, such as the pandemic. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance programs to support small businesses.

variables.Description: Median percentage change in small businesses card revenue through credit and debit card transactions in the city. Registered by Block Inc's data.
variables.Insights: This is informative of the demand for products and services provided by small businesses. City leaders can use this data to target economic support strategies to industries that are underperforming or at risk.

variables.Description: Percentage of occupied office and industrial space by submarket.
variables.Insights: Office and industrial occupancy rate are helpful for understanding work patterns and determining space requirements. Higher vacancy rates decrease the transient population of the Central Business District (CBD) or downtown area, affecting its vibrancy and economy. This indicator can also help Identify commercial assets for conversion to residential use (adaptive reuse) or create incentives for workers to return to the office neighborhood.
variables.Geography: JLL Office and Industrial Real Estate Submarkets

variables.Variable: YTD total net absorption (% of stock)
variables.Description: Stock that has become occupied as a percentage of the stock that was vacant or have been made available in the last year
variables.Insights: If the market has a positive net absorption rate, it means that more space is being leased than is being moved out of. The net absorption can be used to understand the overall health of the real estate market, and therefore, identify distressed office or industrial corridors.
variables.Geography: JLL Office and Industrial Real Estate Submarkets

variables.Description: Average rental price listed by landlords per square foot of office or industrial space.
variables.Insights: Average asking price can be an indicative of the qualities of an area and its demand.
variables.Geography: JLL Office and Industrial Real Estate Submarkets

variables.Description: Total population
variables.Insights: Population growth allows for the expansion of labor and products which then grows the economy. Tracking population trends is key to make better decisions about building new infrastructure and service provision.

variables.Description: Total number of households
variables.Insights: The number of households is useful to understand the composition of the city's population and it's a key denominator to many economic indicators.

variables.Description: Median household income
variables.Insights: Median household income provides information about the financial resources available to households, and is closely tied to employment levels, educational attainment, and health.

variables.Description: Median housing value
variables.Insights: Housing prices are an indicator of the city's desirability and affordability. Changes in housing prices can also be associated with gentrification processes that affect vulnerable households.

variables.Description: Percentage of population above 200% of the poverty line
variables.Insights: Poverty measurement provides essential information about how well the economy is performing overall. It helps us understand financial hardship and the effects of poverty on government, communities, and families.

variables.Description: Percentage of owner-occupied housing units
variables.Insights: Owning a house is key for the wealth-building of families. It promotes independence and financial security, and contributes to economic growth and job creation in the neighborhood.

variables.Description: Percentage of households paying 30% of their salary or more in housing
variables.Insights: Households are considered cost burdened when they spend more than 30% of their income on housing needs. This leaves less disposable income to pay for other needs such as food, transportation, and medical expenses.

variables.Description: Percentage population 25-years and over with a bachelor's degree or higher
variables.Insights: Post-secondary education is more accessible to some than others. Also, college degrees tend to lead to less economic hardship, greater job security and benefits, and greater access to resources that contribute to better health.

variables.Description: Percentage Asian population (non-Hispanic)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Variable: Percentage Black or African American population
variables.Description: Percentage Black or African American population (non-Hispanic)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Percentage Hispanic population (All races)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Percentage white population (non-Hispanic)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Percentage population of other races (not listed above)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Mean travel time to work (in minutes)
variables.Insights: Longer commute times can affect the daily productivity of a person and are likely to be more expensive than shorter ones. Travel time to work can also provide insights into how disconnected some communities are from quality jobs due to the lack of public transportation options or limited road access.

variables.Description: Percentage population under 19 years old
variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Description: Percentage population 20 to 34 years old
variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Description: Percentage population 35 to 44 years old
variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Description: Percentage population 45 to 64 years old
variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Description: Percentage population over 65 years old
variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Description: Number of startups with HQ in Baltimore that went through funding rounds to raise money from the market for its growth or expansion.
variables.Insights: The money raised in a funding round is typically used to hire staff, build out the company's product or service, and expand into new markets. Therefore, this is an indicator of startup growth and investment activity in the city.

variables.Description: Total size of funding rounds (in dollars) for all disclosed amounts. Note: Not all funding rounds disclose their size. Use this indicator with caution.
variables.Insights: The money raised in a funding round is typically used to hire staff, build out the company's product or service, and expand into new markets. Therefore, this is an indicator of startup growth and investment activity in the city.

variables.Description: Number of startups with HQ in Baltimore sold or acquired by an investor.
variables.Insights: An exit occurs when an investor decides to liquidate their stake in a company. Exits indicate when a private equity firm realizes a return on its investment.

variables.Description: Number of startups for each industry with HQ in Phoenix. Note: Some startups are in multiple industries at the same time. Don't use the sum of the values in this chart to estimate the total number of startups in the city.
variables.Insights: This indicator helps understand what industries are growing in the city, and where innovation and investement is concentrated.

config.title: ABOUT THE DATA

variables.Description: Number of unemployed people as a percentage of the labor force (population that is either working or actively looking for work).
variables.Insights: Employment among workforce participants is directly related to economic opportunity. It also indicates if the economy is operating at its full productive potential.
variables.Source: Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS), Economy at a Glance Tables

variables.Description: Number of jobs added or lost compared to selected baseline.
variables.Insights: Knowing the fluctuations in the number of jobs by industry can inform what occupations are in high demand, and could inform workforce development strategies.
variables.Source: Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS), Economy at a Glance Tables

variables.Description: Total amount of dollars spent by consumers in locations registered in SafeGraph's POI credit and debit card transactions data.
variables.Insights: Consumer spending is a key indicative of the current economy and can help identify struggling commercial corridors. This data point can guide strategic investment decisions to improve commercial activity in the city.
variables.Source: Dewey Data, SafeGraph POI transaction data

variables.Description: Total number of credit and debit card transactions in locations registered in SafeGraph's POI data.
variables.Insights: Although consumer spending provides information about the amount of dollars spent, the number of transactions can serve as proxy of demand. A analysis of these two data points provides a more comprehensive look into consumer behavior and commercial activity.
variables.Source: Dewey Data, SafeGraph POI transaction data

variables.Description: Total amount of dollars spent by consumers in tourism-related industry locations registered in SafeGraph's POI credit and debit card transactions data.
variables.Insights: Tourism spending is a key indicative of the tourism activity in the city. This data point can help understand the changes in consumer behavior due to seasonality and develop industry-specific economic strategies.
variables.Source: Dewey Data, SafeGraph POI transaction data

variables.Description: Monthly average percentage of out-of-state consumers in tourism-related industry locations registered in SafeGraph's POI transactions data.
variables.Insights: This data point is helpful to understand the changes in demand of specific tourism-related activities to customers from out of state.
variables.Source: Dewey Data, SafeGraph POI transaction data

variables.Description: Total number of new businesses formed. Collected by Data Axle from secretaries of state, county courthouses, utility providers, departments of revenue, departments of taxation, local business and legal journals, and other sources that record new business transactions.
variables.Insights: New businesses bring jobs and revenue to the local economies by offering local products, paying sales and property tax, and using local vendors and supporting services. This data point is indicative of the conditions the local economy has to foster new businesses, providing insights for the implementation of entrepreneurship support programs.
variables.Source: Data Axle USA New Businesses Dashboard

variables.Description: Perception of businesses that reported rent to be a burden as a monthly expenditure. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: The perception of rent burden among small businesses helps to identify the pressures that puts them at risk of failing. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance to small businesses, create affordable rental commercial properties, provide down payment assistance programs, and more.

variables.Description: Percentage of businesses that reported paying rent in full last month. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: Small businesses failing to pay rent in full and on time are at risk of failing. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance to small businesses, create affordable rental commercial properties, provide down payment assistance programs, and more.

variables.Description: Percentage of businesses that reported paying more on rent now than six months ago. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: Increases in small businesses' rent costs are helpful to identify the pressures that puts them at risk of failing. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance to small businesses, create affordable rental commercial properties, provide down payment assistance programs, and more.

variables.Description: Estimated time businesses reported would be capable to continue operations with cash currently at hand if revenue stopped tomorrow. Collected by Alignable's Small Businesses' poll to their network.
variables.Insights: Understanding cash flow capacity is helpful to identify the level of risk small businesses are at in case of crisis, such as the pandemic. Based on this, city leader can prioritize where to target technical assistance programs to support small businesses.

variables.Description: Median percentage change in small businesses card revenue through credit and debit card transactions in the city. Registered by Block Inc's data.
variables.Insights: This is informative of the demand for products and services provided by small businesses. City leaders can use this data to target economic support strategies to industries that are underperforming or at risk.

variables.Description: Percentage of occupied office and industrial space by submarket.
variables.Insights: Office and industrial occupancy rate are helpful for understanding work patterns and determining space requirements. Higher vacancy rates decrease the transient population of the Central Business District (CBD) or downtown area, affecting its vibrancy and economy. This indicator can also help Identify commercial assets for conversion to residential use (adaptive reuse) or create incentives for workers to return to the office neighborhood.
variables.Geography: JLL Office and Industrial Real Estate Submarkets

variables.Variable: YTD total net absorption (% of stock)
variables.Description: Stock that has become occupied as a percentage of the stock that was vacant or have been made available in the last year
variables.Insights: If the market has a positive net absorption rate, it means that more space is being leased than is being moved out of. The net absorption can be used to understand the overall health of the real estate market, and therefore, identify distressed office or industrial corridors.
variables.Geography: JLL Office and Industrial Real Estate Submarkets

variables.Description: Average rental price listed by landlords per square foot of office or industrial space.
variables.Insights: Average asking price can be an indicative of the qualities of an area and its demand.
variables.Geography: JLL Office and Industrial Real Estate Submarkets

variables.Description: Total population
variables.Insights: Population growth allows for the expansion of labor and products which then grows the economy. Tracking population trends is key to make better decisions about building new infrastructure and service provision.

variables.Description: Total number of households
variables.Insights: The number of households is useful to understand the composition of the city's population and it's a key denominator to many economic indicators.

variables.Description: Median household income
variables.Insights: Median household income provides information about the financial resources available to households, and is closely tied to employment levels, educational attainment, and health.

variables.Description: Median housing value
variables.Insights: Housing prices are an indicator of the city's desirability and affordability. Changes in housing prices can also be associated with gentrification processes that affect vulnerable households.

variables.Description: Percentage of population above 200% of the poverty line
variables.Insights: Poverty measurement provides essential information about how well the economy is performing overall. It helps us understand financial hardship and the effects of poverty on government, communities, and families.

variables.Description: Percentage of owner-occupied housing units
variables.Insights: Owning a house is key for the wealth-building of families. It promotes independence and financial security, and contributes to economic growth and job creation in the neighborhood.

variables.Description: Percentage of households paying 30% of their salary or more in housing
variables.Insights: Households are considered cost burdened when they spend more than 30% of their income on housing needs. This leaves less disposable income to pay for other needs such as food, transportation, and medical expenses.

variables.Description: Percentage population 25-years and over with a bachelor's degree or higher
variables.Insights: Post-secondary education is more accessible to some than others. Also, college degrees tend to lead to less economic hardship, greater job security and benefits, and greater access to resources that contribute to better health.

variables.Description: Percentage Asian population (non-Hispanic)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Variable: Percentage Black or African American population
variables.Description: Percentage Black or African American population (non-Hispanic)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Percentage Hispanic population (All races)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Percentage white population (non-Hispanic)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Percentage population of other races (not listed above)
variables.Insights: Race and ethnicity data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population and better address the needs and existing inequities in the economy.

variables.Description: Mean travel time to work (in minutes)
variables.Insights: Longer commute times can affect the daily productivity of a person and are likely to be more expensive than shorter ones. Travel time to work can also provide insights into how disconnected some communities are from quality jobs due to the lack of public transportation options or limited road access.

variables.Description: Percentage population under 19 years old
variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Description: Percentage population 20 to 34 years old
variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Insights: Age group data are useful to understand the composition of the city's population. It can help city leaders provide better services and implement workforce development programs to the different groups.

variables.Description: Number of startups with HQ in Phoenix that went through funding rounds to raise money from the market for its growth or expansion.
variables.Insights: The money raised in a funding round is typically used to hire staff, build out the company's product or service, and expand into new markets. Therefore, this is an indicator of startup growth and investment activity in the city.

variables.Description: Total size of funding rounds (in dollars) for all disclosed amounts. Note: Not all funding rounds disclose their size. Use this indicator with caution.
variables.Insights: The money raised in a funding round is typically used to hire staff, build out the company's product or service, and expand into new markets. Therefore, this is an indicator of startup growth and investment activity in the city.

variables.Description: Number of startups with HQ in Phoenix sold or acquired by an investor.
variables.Insights: An exit occurs when an investor decides to liquidate their stake in a company. Exits indicate when a private equity firm realizes a return on its investment.

variables.Description: Number of startups for each industry with HQ in Phoenix. Note: Some startups are in multiple industries at the same time. Don't use the sum of the values in this chart to estimate the total number of startups in the city.
variables.Insights: This indicator helps understand what industries are growing in the city, and where innovation and investement is concentrated.

variables.Insights: The money raised in a funding round is typically used to hire staff, build out the company's product or service, and expand into new markets. Therefore, this is an indicator of startup growth and investment activity in the city.

variables.Description: Total size of funding rounds (in dollars) for all disclosed amounts. Note: Not all funding rounds disclose their size. Use this indicator with caution.
variables.Insights: The money raised in a funding round is typically used to hire staff, build out the company's product or service, and expand into new markets. Therefore, this is an indicator of startup growth and investment activity in the city.

variables.Description: Number of startups with HQ in Tampa sold or acquired by an investor.
variables.Insights: An exit occurs when an investor decides to liquidate their stake in a company. Exits indicate when a private equity firm realizes a return on its investment.

variables.Description: Number of startups for each industry with HQ in Tampa. Note: Some startups are in multiple industries at the same time. Don't use the sum of the values in this chart to estimate the total number of startups in the city.
variables.Insights: This indicator helps understand what industries are growing in the city, and where innovation and investement is concentrated.
